The paper deals with shape decomposition, which is a problem commonly studied in computer vision (cs.CV) and computer graphics (cs.GR). The use of a graph-based approach and diffusion processes suggests that the paper may also be relevant to machine learning (cs.AI), as well as graph theory and algorithms (cs.LG) and signal processing (cs.SI).
